<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p4'} the quaternions were discovered by the irish mathematician sir william rowan hamilton

correlations was by sangwine and ell in 19

polarisation state of the optical e
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p11'} in 2001 pei et al. described an algorithm for the quaternion fourier transform,
convolution, and correlation by a 2d complex fast fourier transform.

sequences of coprime lengths to construct a quaternion sequence of length

perfect quaternion sequences of lengths up to 98 which were discovered by the author in 2009.

extended the method of arasu and de launey for constructing perfect arrays
of unbounded size over 4 roots of unity to quaternions.

<title> {} thermal convection in fluidized granular systemsurl
http://www.cec.uchile.cl/cinetica/
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p1'} in the study of granular systems, convection has attracted
particular attention. many of the experimental and simulation
studies of granular convection focus their attention on the
effects of a vibrat
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p2'} the purpose of this letter is to point out the existence of a
convective regime in granular systems when there is no vibrating
base, or any effect caused by the roughness or the angle of the
walls, or
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p3'} more precisely the bottom wall gives
a stochastic normal component to the
velocity of each particle that collides with it.
the tangential velocity is unchanged, thus a shear-free thermal boundary
cond
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p4'} when energy is pumped into a granular system through a
boundary—the bottom wall in the present case—a temperature

<para> {'class': 'ltx_noindent', '{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p2'} neutrinophysik hat in diesem jahrzehnt sehr an popularität gewonnen, nicht zuletzt

alle oszillationsexperimen
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p3'} ein solches steriles neutrino könnte aufgrund seiner gravitativen wechselwirkung sowie
der neutrinooszillationen einen einfluß auf die primordiale nukleosynthese haben.
dieses phänomen ist schon in 
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p4'} während bisherige publikationen sich meistens auf numerische rechnungen beschränkten,

vernachlässigen.
da

model f
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p5'} we present a spatial hybrid systems modeling language, compiler and mesh-free lagrangian based

but describe the mechanisms which quantifiably predict specific observed behavior. since all aspects

progr
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p10'} in order to enable scientists to create mechanistic models easily, we are developing a new

mesoscopic molec
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p11'} mechanica describes models in terms of objects and processes. objects are the physical things being

alleviate the need for users

<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p15'} sbml (http://www.sbml.org/) can describe phenomenon such as chemical reactions in a well-stirred

<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p16'} petri nets are a modeling formalism introduced by carl a. petri to represent chemical

<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p17'} systems biology approaches in general are not ideally suited for describing bio-mechanics, as they

<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p18'} particle based approaches start at the nano rather than system scale and describe natural phenomena
from an atomistic perspective. traditional md simulators model a fixed number of spherical,

<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p19'} reactive md excels at describing the nano-scale, however meso- and multi-scale phenomena present

<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p20'} stochastic particle simulators such as mcell stiles2001monte,

<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p22'} mechanica builds on the tdpd and incorporates reacting particles and discrete events, and defines a

<ERROR> {'class': 'undefined'} \section
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p23'} approachapproach
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p24'} the mechanica modeling language (mml) enables construction of mechanistic models of natural
phenomena. mml is based on a functional subset of microsoft typescript, and includes
conventional constructs
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p25'} mml has two basic constructs: objects and processes, to reflect the objects and processes found in
naturally occurring phenomena. objects in mml can be a conventional primitive type (e.g., scalars,
in
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p26'} mml represents materials as a collection of particle and link objects. mml particles
typically represent “parcels” of small pieces of real materials rather than atoms. links are
persistent structural 
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p27'} processes in mml are different from processes in the traditional computing sense in which processes
typically are a sequence of instructions that define a series of discrete state changes in objects.

<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p28'} discrete processes are similar to events in modelica or sbml. they obey the same semantics as sbml
events, and we evaluate them using the sbml event handling algorithm we developed in
somogyi:2014tv. 
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p29'} continuous processes are a generalization of chemical reactions and define the time evolution of
participating continuous variables such as concentrations, amounts, real or
complex numbers. continuous
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p30'} particles are the basic building blocks of materials. they have a position and optional attributes
such as spatial extent, orientation, mass. they can be point particles or have complex shapes.
links 
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p31'} we can define a simple particle-link system with a pair of point particles, a and
b, located at , and  respectively, and explicitly connect them with a
spring link as
[style=chai]
a:particle(0,0,0,mas
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p32'} a field is a mapping between a value at any spatial location and a set of values
associated with material points. in general, any continuously valued field,  can be
approximated as a sum over a set of

<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p1'} reconstruction of a curve from sample points
(“connect-the-dots”) is an important problem
studied now for twenty years.
early efforts, primarily by researchers in computer vision,
pattern recognition,
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p2'} a breakthrough was achieved by amenta, bern, and
eppstein ,
who designed two algorithms that
guarantee correct reconstruction of smooth closed curves even with
(sufficiently dense)
uniform
samples,
an
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p3'} their work was followed by a flurry of improvements and extensions:
a computational improvement ,
a simpler “nearest-neighbor crust” that raises the density threshold to
 , and
an extention to curves 
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p4'} althaus et al. 
have now implemented all the major curve reconstruction algorithms
using leda ,
and made them available for interactive comparison on the
web.
their experiments show that the tsp algor
<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p5'} the next frontier in provable
reconstruction is reconstruction of 2d surfaces embedded in 3d.
see  for a start.

/home/local/yzan/Desktop/Cleanskin/results/latexml/=quant-ph0001011.xml
<para> {'align': 'center', '{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p1'} bohmian mechanics contradicts quantum mechanics
    
    
    arnold neumaier
    
    
    institut für mathematik, universität wien
    strudlhofgasse 4, a-1090 wien, austria
    email: neum@cma.u
<para> {'class': 'ltx_noindent', '{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p2'} abstract.
<para> {'class': 'ltx_noindent', '{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p3'} it is shown that, for a harmonic oscillator in the ground state,
bohmian mechanics and quantum mechanics predict values of opposite
sign for certain time correlations.
<para> {'class': 'ltx_noindent', '{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p4'} the discrepancy can be explained by the fact that bohmian mechanics
has no natural way to accomodate the heisenberg picture, since the
local expectation values that define the beables of the theory de
<para> {'class': 'ltx_noindent', '{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p5'} relations to measurement are discussed, too, and shown to leave no
loophole for claiming that bohmian mechanics reproduces all
predictions of quantum mechanics exactly.
<para> {'align': 'left', '{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p6'} keywords: bohmian mechanics, quantum mechanics,
pilot wave, causal interpretation, local expectation value,
harmonic oscillator, time correlations
    
    
    1998   pacs classification:
03.65.bz

<para> {'{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id': 'p7'} diffraction in  collisions at the tevatron offers
